{"title":"Pogačar’s second Tour de France Win inspires Colnago Bike Collection","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/21/pogacar-colnago-collection/","date":1626871953000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Want to ride like Tadej Pogačar? That might be a tall order <span>— but with the introduction of its new Capsule Collection, Colnago makes it possible to at least ride <em>a bike</em> like his.&nbsp;</span></p><p>On July 19, Colnago announced it would celebrate the Slovenian’s second straight Tour de France win with a stable of the same bikes he used to win the tour. The livery choices in yellow, white polka dot, and white/black mirror the three leader jerseys <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/06/15/limited-edition-prologo-scratch-m5-saddles-get-signature-treatment-for-tadej-pogacar/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Pogačar</a> won in the TdF.</p><p>The brand says the three bikes in the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/06/02/check-out-colnagos-16400-limited-edition-tour-de-france-v3r/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">V3R</a> Capsule Collection “represent Colnago’s excellence in terms of technological innovation, performance and style.” Campagnolo handles the groupset and wheels, and the total cable integration gives an “aesthetically flawless look.”</p><figure id=\"attachment_266039\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-266039\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173815/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-YELLOW-prospettiva-fondo-nero11.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173815/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-YELLOW-prospettiva-fondo-nero11.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x354/rscb26/ng:webp/ngcb26\" alt=\"special edition colnago v3rs pogacar yellow bike\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1463\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173815/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-YELLOW-prospettiva-fondo-nero11.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 2000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173815/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-YELLOW-prospettiva-fondo-nero11-297x217.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173815/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-YELLOW-prospettiva-fondo-nero11-800x585.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173815/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-YELLOW-prospettiva-fondo-nero11-120x88.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173815/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-YELLOW-prospettiva-fondo-nero11-768x562.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173815/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-YELLOW-prospettiva-fondo-nero11-1536x1124.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173815/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-YELLOW-prospettiva-fondo-nero11-696x509.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173815/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-YELLOW-prospettiva-fondo-nero11-1068x781.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173815/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-YELLOW-prospettiva-fondo-nero11-1920x1404.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173815/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-YELLOW-prospettiva-fondo-nero11-574x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 574w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173815/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-YELLOW-prospettiva-fondo-nero11-80x60.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 80w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px