1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173815/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-YELLOW-prospettiva-fondo-nero11-574x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 574w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173815/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-YELLOW-prospettiva-fondo-nero11-80x60.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 80w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-266039\">Pogačar-inspired V3R Capsule Collection bicycle in yellow livery.</figcaption></figure><h2>“They’re really fast.” Colnago Collection Specs</h2><p>“One of the things I love most about doing well at the Tour is the special bikes Colnago produces for me, the attention to detail is astonishing,”&nbsp;said Pogačar. “I’m glad that other riders can now share this experience with these three special edition bikes celebrating the special three jerseys.”</p><p>Colnago delivers the experience with its ultralight and <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/07/19/colnago-v3rs-disc-road-bike-mixes-carbon-monocoque-with-modern-aerodynamics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">aerodynamic V3R frame</a>, which weighs a scant 790 grams. Pogačar calls out the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/03/14/2019-campagnolo-super-record-eps-adds-12-speed-to-electronic-pro-road-gruppo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Campagnolo Super Record EPS</a> 12-speed disc groupset for its safe braking and fast shifting. The bikes sit on tubeless <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/05/13/review-campy-bora-ultra-wto-45-road-wheels-are-faster-more-versatile-than-ever/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Campagnolo Bora Ultra WTO wheels</a>, which Pogačar uses on the flat. “They’re really fast,” he assesses, then laughs. “I don’t know what to say.”</p><figure id=\"attachment_266040\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-266040\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21.jpg\" alt=\"colnago campagnolo gearset pogacar polka dot\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1587\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21.jpg 2000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21-297x236.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21-800x635.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21-120x95.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21-768x609.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21-1536x1219.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21-696x552.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21-1068x847.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21-1920x1524.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21-529x420.jpg 529w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21.jpg 2000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21-297x236.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21-800x635.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21-120x95.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21-768x609.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21-1536x1219.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21-696x552.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21-1068x847.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21-1920x1524.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173917/V3Rs-TDF-POGA-POIS-particolare-21-529x420.jpg 529w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-266040\">Detail of Colnago’s Pogačar-inspired bike in white polka dot livery.</figcaption></figure><p>We wouldn’t either. Fresh off his second straight TdF win, in which the 22-year-old dusted the field with a 5:20 victory margin, he’s clearly just happy. The first thing he says about the Colnago Collection’s yellow jersey livery?</p><p>“I especially like this one because it’s yellow.” He flashes an impish grin to his camera crew, then refocuses on the bike in front of him.</p><figure id=\"attachment_266038\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-266038\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1.jpg\" alt=\"tadej pogacar tour podium win\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1.jpg 2000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1-1920x1280.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1.jpg 2000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1-1920x1280.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20173545/bettiniphoto_0527762_1_originali1-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-266038\">Pogačar takes the podium at 2021’s Tour de France. c. Colnago, all Tour images by <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/bettiniphoto/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Bettini Photo</a></figcaption></figure><h2>Bonus Swag and MSRP</h2><p>As a bonus, Colnago will include a jersey signed by Pogačar with each bike. Of course, the jersey will correspond to the bike’s livery.</p><p>Want to be the Tour’s best young rider? The best climber on the Grande Boucle? The overall winner? With help from Pogačar and Colnago, now you can dress the part.Each bike in Colnago’s V3R Capsule Collection retails for the same <span>$16,690</span> / 14,090€ / £12,090.</p><p><em><a href=\"https://www.colnago.com/en/capsulecollection/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Colnago.com</a></em></p></div></div>","author":"Sam Anderson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"29894c37d873904d11c683edd908454171e3205195cfef483782088221e35e69","category":"Cycling"}